</description><pubDate>Wed, 26 Mar 2014 10:00:10 -0700</pubDate><guid>http://www.spokesman.com/blogs/tech-deck/2014/mar/26/oculus-bought-facebook-why-oh-why/</guid></item><item><title>Get your name on the EVE monument</title><link>http://www.spokesman.com/blogs/tech-deck/2014/feb/18/get-your-name-on-the-eve-monument/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://eve.com/monument"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="http://i.imgur.com/tRPcMaM.jpg" style="width: 480px; height: 285px;" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Players of the game EVE Online have the opportunity to have their character name &lt;a href="http://eve.com/monument"&gt;permanently etched in stone&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you&amp;#39;ve never played EVE Online, just imagine the biggest, most in-depth space sim you can imagine. Then make it bigger. Then multiply that by the 10 years that the game has been online and evolving. It&amp;#39;s seriously huge and old and intense. And awesome.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, if your character is active as of March 1, 2014, your player character name will be engraved in stone for all of Iceland to look at and snicker.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That is seriously awesome.&lt;/p&gt;

